{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Tit|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"Remind them to submit to rulers and authorities, to obey, to be ready for every good work,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"to slander no one, to avoid fighting, and to be kind, always showing gentleness to all people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"For we too were once foolish, disobedient, deceived, enslaved by various passions and pleasures, living in malice and envy, hateful, detesting one another.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"But when the kindness of God our Savior and his love for mankind appeared,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"he saved us —not by works of righteousness that we had done, but according to his mercy —through the washing of regeneration and renewal by the Holy Spirit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"He poured out his Spirit on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Savior","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"so that, having been justified by his grace, we may become heirs with the hope of eternal life.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"This saying is trustworthy. I want you to insist on these things, so that those who have believed God might be careful to devote themselves to good works. These are good and profitable for everyone.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"But avoid foolish debates, genealogies, quarrels, and disputes about the law, because they are unprofitable and worthless.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"Reject a divisive person after a first and second warning.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"For you know that such a person has gone astray and is sinning; he is self-condemned.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"When I send Artemas or Tychicus to you, make every effort to come to me in Nicopolis, because I have decided to spend the winter there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"Diligently help Zenas the lawyer and Apollos on their journey, so that they will lack nothing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"Let our people learn to devote themselves to good works for pressing needs, so that they will not be unfruitful.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","bookOrder":55,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"All those who are with me send you greetings. Greet those who love us in the faith. Grace be with all of you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Tit","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,12,14],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Christian Living among Outsiders"},{"beforeVerse":12,"text":"Final Instructions and Closing"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Remind them to submit "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 13:1–7","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:13","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" to rulers and authorities, to obey, to be ready for every good work, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 13:1–7","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":1},{"label":"1Pt 2:13","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"to slander no one, to avoid fighting, and to be kind, always showing gentleness "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 3:13","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to all people. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jms 3:13","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Tit:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For we too were once foolish, disobedient, deceived, enslaved by various passions "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 1:4","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 2:10","book":"2Pe","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and pleasures, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jm